The paper discusses a template poisoning attack on biometric systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attack is specifically targeted towards face recognition pipelines based on deep neural networks, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of adversarial samples and transferability of attacks, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a countermeasure for detecting the attack, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves analyzing feature space.
